Name: Twilight Templar
Description: As a deadly cloaked assassin, Dark Templar has sacrificed himself to get a stable source of void psionic. He can use Shadow Asylum, Shadow Pace, and Dark Souls, and use green <Void Psionic>to attack his enemies.**Can attack the ground**

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target area or follow the target unit. Moving units will not engage enemies.
Root.Name: Move

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to cancel all orders and stop moving.
Root.Name: Stop

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to stay where they are and attack enemies that are within range. Units will neither chase down enemies nor move to engage.
Root.Name: Hold Position

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target point, fighting nearby enemies along the way. Targeting a unit with the Attack command orders that it be attacked until it is destroyed.
Root.Name: Attack

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to patrol between their current position and the target area. Units will attack enemies and move to engage nearby enemies.
Root.Name: Patrol

Root.Tooltip: Twilight Templar will blink forward for a short distance. If there is a enemy unit within the path, this will deal 20 damage to it and stun it for 1 second.
Root.Name: Shadow Pace

Root.Tooltip: Twilight Templar is permanently invisible and has almost no energy recovery ability. When Twilight Templar is attacked with more than 20 points of damage, 99% of the damage is reduced, and it is invincible for the next 1 second. It will be consumed Twilight Templar 20 points of energy every time Shadow Asylum is triggered.
Root.Name: Shadow Asylum

Root.Tooltip: Twilight Templar's attack can cause damage to all enemy units within range and stuns them for 1 second.
Root.Name: Blade of Exile

Root.Tooltip: Teleports the Dark Templar to a nearby target location. Ability can only be used once every 20 seconds.
Root.Name: Shadow Stride

Root.Tooltip: Sacrifices 2 Templar to create an Archon.**Can attack ground and air units**
Root.Name: Archon Merge

Root.Tooltip: Jump from target to target, dealing 20 (+15 vs. Light) damage with each jump. Hits 1 times.
Root.Name: Shadow Fury

Root.Tooltip: This ability unlocks at Commander Level 6.
Root.Name: Blink

Root.Tooltip:
Places target unit or structure in stasis for 10 seconds, disabling the unit for the duration of the effect. Units and structures in stasis cannot be attacked or affected by abilities.

Can target structures or ground units.
Root.Name: Void Stasis

Root.Tooltip: This ability unlocks at Commander Level 6.
Root.Name: Void Stasis

Root.Tooltip: Jump from target to target, dealing 20 (+15 vs. Light) damage with each jump. Hits 1 times.
Root.Name: Shadow Fury

Root.Tooltip: Twilight Templar deals 50% additional damage when attacking units affected by stuns, slows, and other negative effects.
Root.Name: Shade Slaughter

Root.Tooltip: Increase the maximum shield of Twilight Templar by 50%, and Dark Souls no longer needs Twilight Templar for continuous guidance.
Root.Name: Intersection of Light and Shadow

Root.Tooltip: Twilight Templar will project Dark Souls to enemy non-heroic ground unit and control it for 10 seconds. You can cast Dark Teleport ahead of the time or wait until Dark Souls ends to teleport non-heroic units near the targets to Twilight Templar's nearby.
Root.Name: Dark Souls

Root.Tooltip: Pre-activate Dark Souls' area teleport.
Root.Name: Dark Teleport

Root.Tooltip: Drops the current order without performing it, and allows you to select a different order.
Root.Name: Cancel
